headlines.description: — Kevin Durant had 31 points, James Harden scored 16 of his 28 points in the fourth quarter and the Brooklyn Nets won their fifth straight game, beating the Toronto Raptors 116-103 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 31 points, Nets beat Raptors for 5th straight

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Ricky Rubio scored a career-high 37 to help the Cleveland Cavaliers outlast the New York Knicks 126-109 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ricky Rubio has career-high 37 points, Cavaliers beat Knicks

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony scored 10 of his season-high 33 points in the fourth quarter and keyed a game-closing 24-11 run that helped the Orlando Magic rally past the Utah Jazz 107-100 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony scores season-best 33, Magic rallies past Jazz

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 30 points and the Washington Wizards beat the Milwaukee Bucks 101-94 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal scores 30 points to help Wizards beat Bucks, 101-94

headlines.description: — Caris LeVert scored 22 points and the Indiana Pacers held on after blowing a 15-point lead, beating the Sacramento Kings 94-91 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers hold off Kings for first win in Sacramento since 2018

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The Oklahoma City Thunder seem to wake up when they get down by double digits.
headlines.shortLinkText: Muscala scores 20, Oklahoma City rallies to beat Spurs 99-94

events.name: Houston Rockets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored 15 of his 25 points in the first quarter and the Golden State Warriors beat the Houston Rockets 120-107 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole has 25 points, NBA-leading Warriors beat Rockets

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 20 points, Reggie Jackson added 19 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Charlotte Hornets 120-106 on Sunday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Jackson lead Clippers past Hornets, 120-106
